# Cordon runtime policy. Read by the hooks (overridable with the
# CORDON_POLICY environment variable).
#
#   strict — file mutations outside an isolated worktree are DENIED.
#            The session must run in `claude --worktree` (or Claude must
#            enter one via the EnterWorktree tool) before edits work.
#   guided — un-isolated sessions get a warning and a recommendation,
#            but edits in the main checkout are allowed. .git/.claude and
#            the Bash escape hatches stay blocked either way.
CORDON_POLICY=strict
